result.text: CLEVELAND , Nov. 12, 2025 /PRNewswire/ -- TransDigm Group Incorporated (NYSE: TDG), a leading global designer, producer and supplier of highly engineered aircraft components, today reported results for the fourth quarter ended September 30, 2025. Fourth quarter highlights include: Net sales of $2,437 million, up 12% from $2,185 million in the prior year's quarter; Net income of $609 million, up 30% from the prior year's quarter; Earnings per share of $7.75, up 34% from the prior year's quarter; EBITDA As Defined of $1,320 million, up 15% from $1,149 million in the prior year's quarter; EBITDA As Defined margin of 54.2%, up 1.6% from the prior year's quarter margin of 52.6%; and Adjusted earnings per share of $10.82, up 10% from $9.83 in the prior year's quarter.
